quiring complex transformation code"]],[[0,[],0,"No-code data stores, that turn offline data (like CSVs and batch files) into powerful REST microservices.  (We call these "Casks")."]],[[0,[],0,"A "],[0,[0],1,"BYO Data Model"],[0,[],0," approach to serving and consuming large datasets on your own terms."]],[[0,[],0,"Fully automated "],[0,[1],1,"data catalog and lineage"],[0,[],0," for all your enterprise data."]]]],[1,"p",[[0,[],0,"Now, onto the new stuff - what's in 0.19?"]]],[1,"h2",[[0,[],0,"Parallel work distribution"]]],[1,"p",[[0,[],0,"This one's really exciting.  For large workloads where customers are running reports that have heavy transformations & enrichments, those workloads used to take some time.  "]]],[1,"p",[[0,[],0,"Now, Vyne can distribute the work transparently over a cluster of nodes.  This gives near-linear reduction in time.  (ie., running a cluster of 3 nodes reduces the time to complete to roughly 1/3rd)."]]],[10,0],[1,"p",[[0,[2],1,"Release Notes"],[0,[],0,"   |   "],[0,[3],1,"Documentation"]]],[1,"h2",[[0,[],0,"Continuous Queries"]]],[1,"p",[[0,[],0,"Vyne has always been great at fetching data over REST from HTTP services, transforming and enriching it as required."]]],[1,"p",[[0,[],0,"However, we now support streaming results from continuous queries - queries that have infinite results.  Using Taxi's new"],[0,[4],0," "],[0,[5],1,"Stream<T>"],[0,[],1," syntax"],[0,[],0,", Vyne can fetch data from any services that expose a "],[0,[5],1,"Stream"],[0,[],0," of data.  "]]],[1,"p",[[0,[],0,"Currently, we support services that expose "],[0,[5],1,"text/event-stream"],[0,[],0," response types, but support for message brokers (such as Kafka) is coming soon."]]],[1,"p",[[0,[],0,"Of course, continuous queries still have the full power of Vyne's transformations and enrichments.  This means  you can subscribe for a feed of data, and seamlessly transform to the shape you require, including asking for data stitched in from other services - all with a single taxiQL query - no integration code required - neat huh?"]]],[10,1],[1,"p",[[0,[6],1,"Release Notes"],[0,[],0," | "],[0,[7],1,"Documentation"]]],[1,"h2",[[0,[],0,"Continuous feeds from Casks"]]],[1,"p",[[0,[],0,"Casks are our lightweight data store - a simple way to take data, and expose it as a fully fledged RESTful microservice."]]],[1,"p",[[0,[],0,"We now support issu streaming updates from Casks as they come in, allowing you to turn RESTful API into a full event stream."]]],[1,"p",[[0,[],0,"We also correctly auto-generate the schema information required to expose these streaming endpoints as "],[0,[5],1,"Stream"],[0,[],0," endpoints, so that Casks can be used as a source for a Continuous Query."]]],[1,"p",[[0,[8],1,"Release Notes"],[0,[],0," | "],[0,[9],1,"Documentation"]]],[1,"h2",[[0,[],0,"Cask data retention policies"]]],[1,"p",[[0,[],0,"Casks are a great place to turn offline data into queryable content.  However, like all data stores, sometimes you want to only keep data for a short term."]]],[1,"p",[[0,[],0,"Cask retention policies have you covered - letting you optionally specify a duration to keep data."]]],[1,"p",[[0,[10],1,"Release Notes"],[0,[],0," | "],[0,[11],1,"Documentation"]]],[1,"h2",[[0,[],0,"New docs site"]]],[1,"p",[[0,[],0,"We have a new documentation site, over at "],[0,[12],1,"docs.vyne.co"],[0,[],0,".  We've migrated our documentation infrastructure away from Gitbook, and onto a Netlify Gatsby stack.  This allows us to keep our docs in our code, and maintain documentation as we go."]]],[10,2],[1,"p",[[0,[],0,"We're working on improving our docs all the time, and this is a big step in the right direction."]]],[1,"h2",[[0,[],0,"Support for HTTP Authentication headers"]]],[1,"p",[[0,[],0,"Vyne can now be configured to pass additional HTTP Authentication headers when calling services."]]],[1,"p",[[0,[],0,"Configuration is defined per-service, and can be a mix of explicitly configured values, or values passed into Vyne through config and environment variables, to help keep your credentials secure."]]],[1,"p",[[0,[13],1,"Release Notes"],[0,[],0," | "],[0,[14],1,"Documentation "]]],[1,"h2",[[0,[],0,"Take it for a spin"]]],[1,"p",[[0,[],0,"Vyne 0.19 is out today, and we can't wait for people to give it a spin.  It's easy to get started with our docker images - simply start up Vyne:"]]],[10,3],[1,"p",[[0,[],0,"As always, "],[0,[15],1,"we're available on Slack"],[0,[],0," to answer any questions - just reach out and say Hello!"]]]]}

